According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Gigabit Internet Service Market was valued at USD 15,577 million in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 17,973 million in 2026 to USD 39,305 million by 2034, registering a CAGR of 14.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth driven by increasing demand for ultra-fast broadband, large-scale fiber-to-the-home (FTTH) deployments, government-backed digital infrastructure initiatives, and rising adoption of cloud computing, AI applications, and smart city technologies. Strong policy support through the European Commission's Gigabit Society programme and expanding public-private partnerships are accelerating the rollout of gigabit connectivity across urban and rural regions. 
